nhc_headline: ...PRISCILLA A LITTLE STRONGER WHILE MOVING SLOWLY... ...HEAVY RAINFALL AND GUSTY WINDS POSSIBLE FOR COASTAL SOUTHWESTERN MEXICO...
summary: ...PRISCILLA A LITTLE STRONGER WHILE MOVING SLOWLY... ...HEAVY RAINFALL AND GUSTY WINDS POSSIBLE FOR COASTAL SOUTHWESTERN MEXICO... As of 11:00 AM MST Sun Oct 05 the center of Priscilla was located near 16.5, -107.1 with movement NNW at 2 mph. The minimum central pressure was 989 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 70 mph.
